# Project: Stu Yam Personal Website

## Tech Stack
- **Static Site Generator**: Jekyll
- **CSS Framework**: Tailwind CSS
- **Hosting**: GitHub Pages

## Project Structure
- `_config.yml`: Jekyll configuration
- `_layouts/`: Page layouts (e.g., default.html, post.html)
- `_posts/`: Blog posts in markdown format
- `index.html`: Homepage
- `assets/css/style.tailwindcss`: Tailwind CSS source file
- `assets/css/style.css`: Compiled CSS (generated by Tailwind)

## Key Technologies
1. **Jekyll**: Ruby-based static site generator
   - Uses Liquid templating engine
   - Processes markdown files in `_posts/` directory
   - Plugins: jekyll-feed, jekyll-tailwindcss, jekyll-cache-bust

2. **Tailwind CSS**: Utility-first CSS framework
   - Source: `assets/css/style.tailwindcss`
   - Compilation handled by jekyll-tailwindcss plugin
   - Custom colors used: sky, emerald, yellow, rose, violet, cyan
   - Dark theme with gradient backgrounds

## Development
- Run local server: `bundle exec jekyll serve`
- Watch for changes: Jekyll auto-regenerates on file updates
- Base URL: https://stuyam.com

## Design Patterns
- Uses gradient backgrounds (slate-950 to cyan-950)
- Color-coded sections for different types of content
- Responsive design with Tailwind's responsive prefixes (md:)
- Floating animations for decorative elements
- Custom hue-rotation effects on images

## When Editing
- Keep consistent styling with existing Tailwind utility classes
- Maintain the color scheme: sky, emerald, yellow, rose, violet, cyan
- Follow the existing layout pattern in index.html
- Use relative paths for internal links

